# Yocto Support for systemd

Yocto provides:

```bitbake
inherit systemd
```

This class automatically handles:

* Installing service files
* Enabling services
* Packaging service units
* Managing dependencies

---

# Basic Recipe Example

```bitbake
DESCRIPTION = "My Application"

LICENSE = "MIT"

SRC_URI += "file://myapp.service"

inherit systemd

SYSTEMD_SERVICE:${PN} = "myapp.service"

do_install() {
    install -d ${D}${systemd_system_unitdir}

    install -m 0644 \
        ${WORKDIR}/myapp.service \
        ${D}${systemd_system_unitdir}/
}
```

---

# Important Variables

## SYSTEMD_SERVICE:${PN}

Specifies which service should be managed.

Example:

```bitbake
SYSTEMD_SERVICE:${PN} = "myapp.service"
```

Multiple services:

```bitbake
SYSTEMD_SERVICE:${PN} = " \
    service1.service \
    service2.service \
"
```

---

## SYSTEMD_AUTO_ENABLE

Controls whether the service starts automatically at boot.

### Enable Service

```bitbake
SYSTEMD_AUTO_ENABLE = "enable"
```

---

### Disable Service

```bitbake
SYSTEMD_AUTO_ENABLE = "disable"
```

Default behavior depends on the recipe and distribution configuration.

---

## inherit systemd

Enables systemd support.

```bitbake
inherit systemd
```

Required whenever systemd services are used.

---

# Service File Location

Systemd service files are installed into:

```text
/lib/systemd/system/
```

In Yocto:

```bitbake
${systemd_system_unitdir}
```

Usually expands to:

```text
/lib/systemd/system
```

---

# Example Service File

```ini
[Unit]
Description=Temperature Monitoring Service
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
ExecStart=/usr/bin/temp-monitor
Restart=always
RestartSec=5

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

---

# Installing Service File

```bitbake
do_install() {
    install -d ${D}${systemd_system_unitdir}

    install -m 0644 \
        ${WORKDIR}/temp-monitor.service \
        ${D}${systemd_system_unitdir}/
}
```

---

# Enable Service at Boot

```bitbake
inherit systemd

SYSTEMD_SERVICE:${PN} = "temp-monitor.service"

SYSTEMD_AUTO_ENABLE = "enable"
```

Result:

```bash
systemctl enable temp-monitor.service
```

is effectively performed during image creation.

---

# Multiple Services Example

```bitbake
inherit systemd

SYSTEMD_SERVICE:${PN} = " \
    mqtt.service \
    logger.service \
    watchdog.service \
"

SYSTEMD_AUTO_ENABLE = "enable"
```

All listed services are enabled.

