# Real-World Yocto Example

Directory structure:

```text
meta-custom/
└── recipes-apps/
    └── temp-monitor/
        ├── temp-monitor.bb
        └── files/
            └── temp-monitor.service
```

Recipe:

```bitbake
DESCRIPTION = "Temperature Monitor"

LICENSE = "MIT"

SRC_URI += "file://temp-monitor.service"

inherit systemd

SYSTEMD_SERVICE:${PN} = "temp-monitor.service"

SYSTEMD_AUTO_ENABLE = "enable"

do_install:append() {
    install -d ${D}${systemd_system_unitdir}

    install -m 0644 \
        ${WORKDIR}/temp-monitor.service \
        ${D}${systemd_system_unitdir}/
}
```

Result:

* Service installed into `/lib/systemd/system`
* Enabled automatically
* Starts on every boot
* Restarted automatically if configured

